HEADWORD: Subcommittee
<hw>Sub`com*mit"tee</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An under
committee; a part or division of a committee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yet by their sequestrators and <qex>subcommittees</qex> abroad . .
. those orders were commonly disobeyed.</q>
